The code used:
    private static final String FETCH_ORDER_BY_CODE_AND_USER = "SELECT {o.pk} FROM {Order AS o} WHERE {o.code} = ?code AND {o.user} = ?user";

    @Override
    public OrderModel getOrderDetailsForCodeAndUser(String code, UserModel user) {
        final FlexibleSearchQuery query = new FlexibleSearchQuery(FETCH_ORDER_BY_CODE_AND_USER);
        query.addQueryParameter("code", code);
        query.addQueryParameter("user", user);
        final SearchResult<OrderModel> result = flexibleSearchService.search(query);
        LOG.info(String.format("Query to get order details for code and user :: %s", query));
        if(CollectionUtils.isEmpty(result.getResult())) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(String.format("Order with code :: %s for the user :: %s not found", code, user.getUid()));
        }
        return result.getResult().get(0);
    }
ISSUE:
  Unable to get the results. returns exception

FIX:
1. Run the query in hac to check if you are able to get the result . If No correct the query. Note: Above code working fine on HAC
2. add query.setDisableSearchRestrictions(true); in the code. This fix my issue

Corrected code:
    @Override
    public OrderModel getOrderDetailsForCodeAndUser(String code, UserModel user) {
        final FlexibleSearchQuery query = new FlexibleSearchQuery(FETCH_ORDER_BY_CODE_AND_USER);
        query.addQueryParameter("code", code);
        query.addQueryParameter("user", user);
        query.setDisableSearchRestrictions(true);
        final SearchResult<OrderModel> result = flexibleSearchService.search(query);
        LOG.info(String.format("Query to get order details for code and user :: %s", query));
        if(CollectionUtils.isEmpty(result.getResult())) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(String.format("Order with code :: %s for the user :: %s not found", code, user.getUid()));
        }
        return result.getResult().get(0);
    }

